caption: I like the whole exterior look of the place, the black and modern look. This made me take a look inside because I don't tend to pay any attention to pizza placing in the city. The pizza here looks great, but I went for the sandwiches for something new.  The Lazzo, this sandwich is filled will a lot of Italian meats (Salami, Capicola, Mortadella) and Provolone. The sandwich is very good, but expect it to be salty because of the types of meat. It is something I would recommend but personally I will only buy this once for fun and to try something new. Great sandwich overall... Next time I must try the pizza!

Love this place. I have been coming here every other day for my steak sandwich. And , as good as it is every time, I have to mention service. Guys there will go above and beyond to make you feel welcome. It is always nice to come back there! Bread is always crispy and fresh, meat-juicy .Prices are normal for this area.
Quick, delicious, convenient for a high quality downtown lunch. Friendly staff too.

I have no images to share because I devoured the breakfast sandwich, coffee and anise biscotti too quickly and once I was midway through I didn’t care to share it’s visual splendor; I did care to share my experience.  Egg white, sharp provolone, mushroom and drizzled  of salt where placed . The bread was soft and thick as a cloud and it surprisingly complimented the simplistic ingredients (Egg white, sharp provolone, mushroom and salt) that housed rich flavors. In honestly, I paused about 7 times trying to comprehend it’s so deliciousness.  Not to be obscene but this is the kind of meal you have after having and intimate night and or morning.  Superb!

This place is price wise on par with most other lunch spots around. I ordered a porchetta sandwich and thought it was a good deal for the price. The meat was juicy but not dripping, which I prefer. It was cut a little thick for porchetta and because of that some slices had large pieces of fat. Otherwise, it had great flavor and was cooked well, really nice finished with some olive oil and sea salt on top. I only saw the sides but they all looked good and I hope to give them a try soon.

We came here to try this new restaurant today. Super disappointed: We ordered chicken and two sides, they only gave us one side. (Eggplant was missing); The chicken was very tiny compared to Eatly and field good chicken; The food tasted bland.  Overall Not Recommend!
